== Screwduino README ==

The Screwduino is an Arduino compatible microcontroller board. It is based on the Arduino UNO but with some improvements. The Screwduino adds screw terminals for outputs and an I2C jack for displays. It has greatly improved mounting holes.

The files in this folder are the ExpressPCB schematic and layout files. The board is layed out to work with the miniboard option and has two Screwduinos per board for a total of 6 board at around $85 or around $14 a board.

